            "id": "4618046",
            "title": "Dell in focus as Citi adds 90-day catalyst watch",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Dell Technologies (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DELL\" title=\"Dell Technologies Inc.\">DELL</a></span>) was in focus on Friday as Citi added a 90-day catalyst watch to the technology giant.</li>\n<li>Shares rose fractionally in premarket trading.</li>\n<li>“We are opening an upside Catalyst Watch on DELL ahead of its July-Q earnings report,” analyst Asiya Merchant wrote in a note to clients. “Our conviction has increased that enterprise IT infrastructure spending continues to strengthen, supported by ongoing AI-related investments, server refresh cycles, and broader demand for data center capacity. We see upside driven by a larger CPU total addressable market (TAM), robust server demand, and continued strength in AI infrastructure deployments, which support stronger growth.”</li>\n<li>Merchant has a Buy rating and a $515 price target on Dell.</li>\n</ul>\n\n</body></html>",
